The article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney aboard Air Force One en route to Galesburg, IL. Carney discusses President Obama's upcoming economic address at Knox College in Galesburg, where he will lay out his vision for the economy and the importance of a thriving middle class. Carney also mentions that the President will visit the Missouri Innovation Campus, which provides students with an integrated academic experience and prepares them for high-paying careers. Carney addresses questions about Edward Snowden's status and the President's opinion on Eliot Spitzer and Anthony Weiner. He also comments on the President's frustration with the House's handling of immigration reform and responds to criticism of the President's speech. Carney confirms personnel changes in the National Economic Council.